abstract: Ukraine reopens fraud case against Yulia V Tymonshenko, opposition leader who is already serving seven-year sentence on charges that have been condemned in the West as politically motivated; reopened case, which dates back 15 years, alleges that she embezzled about $3 million from federal budget and evaded paying about $2.5 million in taxes.
snippet: The general prosecutor’s office in Ukraine on Monday said that it had reopened another criminal case against Yulia V. Tymoshenko.
lead_paragraph: The general prosecutor’s office in Ukraine on Monday said that it had reopened another criminal case against Yulia V. Tymoshenko.

headline.seo: Ukraine Reopens Case on Yulia Tymoshenko
